Call to Arms - teamwork skill
------------------------------------------------------------
Although many swashbucklers are loners, all are bound to
each other by mutual respect.  When swashbucklers come
together to fight as a team, each becomes more effective
than he would be individually.  The more swashbucklers
gather, the greater the improvement when they fight in
tandem.  When a group of swashbucklers gather, one of them,
usually the leader, will issue a call to arms.  Each
swashbuckler who hears the call will join in, both adding
to and sharing in the benefits of the call.  Swashbucklers
who cannot give the call to arms due to inexperience can
still add to the effect of others' calls, while benefitting
themselves.  Once the call is made, the effect will
continue for the duration even if the group disperses. The
effect of the original call to arms can be renewed
periodically in a smaller group, as long as it is done
before the effect expires.

GL:  5
SP: 30
command:  scall
duration: long
